nodes.bodyText:
@sbordet the CoreSession close takes a callback, we fail the callback which indicates that the frame was not sent. If you don't care about whether the frame was sent or not you can give it NOOP and ignore the result.
In that case for this method we could not use the BlockingCallback altogether and just go:
coreSession.close(closeCode, reasonPhrase, NOOP);

