nodes.bodyText:
@gregw good point! But perhaps AutoLock is enough then?
void send(ByteBuffer) 
{
  try (AutoLock lock = _lock.lock()) // Provides exclusion.
  {
    BlockingCallback c = new BlockingCallback();
    send(..., c);
    c.block(); // Provides blocking semantic.
  }
}
Concurrent close from different threads is now handled by the AtomicBoolean guard so it won't deadlock. We may still want to exclude a send() and a close().

